---
name: scljet-multitable-mutate
description: SclJet delete a row from one table of a multi-table database, preserving the others and reassigning root pages (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet multi-table mutate

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, TableSpec, buildMultiTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[deleteRowidsInTable](std/scljet/mutate.ssc)

```scalascript
// Three tables in one file. Delete rowid 2 (the sku=200 row) from table index 1
// (products): that table's tree is rebuilt, the other tables pass through as raw
// records, and every table's schema-record rootpage is re-encoded for the new
// layout. Reference integrity_check accepts the result; int and JS agree.
val tables = List(
  TableSpec("users", "CREATE TABLE users(id INTEGER, name TEXT)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("alice")), List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob")))),
  TableSpec("products", "CREATE TABLE products(sku INTEGER, title TEXT)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(100L), SqlText("widget")), List(SqlInteger(200L), SqlText("gadget")), List(SqlInteger(300L), SqlText("gizmo")))),
  TableSpec("orders", "CREATE TABLE orders(oid INTEGER, total INTEGER)",
    List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlInteger(4200L)))))

buildMultiTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, tables) match
  case Right(db) =>
    deleteRowidsInTable(db, 2, 1, 1, List(2L)) match
      case Right(newDb) => println((newDb.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(newDb).toString)
      case Left(message) => println("MUTATE-ERROR:" + message)
  case Left(error) => println("BUILD-ERROR:" + error.message)
```
